 SEMINAR/DEMONSTRATION

 April 14 at Sisir Mancha; 6 pm: Taru Shruti, in collaboration with ministry of culture, government of India, hosts Ashoketaru-Sandhya, an evening of seminar and demonstration on some of the pioneering ventures of the Rabindrasangeet maestro. Highlighting his efforts to promote (1) first solo recital in Rabindrasangeet; (2) first staging of Tagores prose plays with songs in the form of shruti natak; (3) his technique in teaching Rabindrasangeet; and (4) excerpts from Valmiki Pratibha. Participants: Partho Ghosh, Gouri Ghosh, Debashis Roychowdhury and disciples of Ashoketaru Bandyopadhyay. Concept and direction: Koushiki Bandyopadhyay. 

